<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>Pavel on DevOps</title><link href="http://pavel.ondevops.com/" rel="alternate"></link><link href="http://pavel.ondevops.com/feeds/all.atom.xml" rel="self"></link><id>http://pavel.ondevops.com/</id><updated>2013-12-22T01:40:37+02:00</updated><entry><title>CLI utility for simple S3 hosting</title><link href="http://pavel.ondevops.com/cli-utility-for-simple-s3-hosting.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2013-12-22T01:40:37+02:00</updated><author><name>Pavel Suchman</name></author><id>tag:pavel.ondevops.com,2013-12-22:cli-utility-for-simple-s3-hosting.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h1&gt;A utility that configures S3 and Route53 to host a static website on your domain.&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Features:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creates a bucket and a route53 record that points to it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Takes care of creating new hosted zone if needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports &lt;a href="http://aws.typepad.com/aws/2012/12/root-domain-website-hosting-for-amazon-s3.html"&gt;Root Domain Website Hosting&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Requirements:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Any system with python and pip.&lt;br /&gt;
Tested on Ubuntu 13.10 Desktop.&lt;br /&gt;
The boto credentials have to be &lt;a href="http://boto.readthedocs.org/en/latest/getting_started.html"&gt;discoverable&lt;/a&gt; via environment variables, ~/.boto file or IAM role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Installation:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;sudo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;pip&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;install&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;boto&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mf"&gt;2.21.0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="n"&gt;wget&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;https&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;//raw.github.com/flypunk/s3host/master/s3host -O s3host&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="n"&gt;chmod&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;s3host&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h2&gt;Usage:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;./s3host domainname&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Feedback and pull requests are welcome! &lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="aws"></category><category term="s3"></category><category term="route53"></category><category term="hosting"></category><category term="cli"></category></entry></feed>